'''Paul Martin Shields''' (born 15 August 1981 in [[Dunfermline]]) is a [[Scotland|Scottish]] [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[striker]] for [[<U+00D6>stersunds FK]].

==Career==
Shields began his career in [[Kirkcaldy]] with [[Raith Rovers F.C.|Raith Rovers]] before earning a <U+00A3>100,000 move to [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] in March 2000. Shields made one substitute appearance for the Parkhead side towards the end of the season, being loaned to [[Albion Rovers F.C.|Albion Rovers]] in the early stages of the [[2000-01 in Scottish football|2000<U+2013>01 season]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/scotland/949496.stm|title=Smith leads transfer moves|date=2000-09-30|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=2008-09-12}}</ref> Following his return in December 2000, Shields failed to add to his solitary appearance for Celtic and was loaned out again in February 2002 to [[Clydebank F.C.|Clydebank]]. At the start of the following season, Shields undertook his third loan spell, this time with [[Queen of the South F.C.|Queen of the South]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/scotland/2204158.stm|title=Shields signs for Queens|date=2002-08-19|accessdate=2008-09-12 | work=BBC News}}</ref> and when he returned to [[Celtic Park]] in January 2003, he was promptly released, joining [[Clyde F.C.|Clyde]] on a short-term deal.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/c/clyde/2723555.stm|title=Clyde sign Shields|date=2003-02-04|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=2008-09-12}}</ref> With no permanent deal on offer,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_div_1/3008825.stm|title=Hagen re-signs for Clyde|date=2003-05-07|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=2008-09-12}}</ref> Shields joined [[Forfar Athletic F.C.|Forfar Athletic]] on a one-year deal in July 2003,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_div_1/3092919.stm|title=Forfar snap up Shields|date=2003-07-24|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=2008-09-12}}</ref> subsequently agreeing a new two-year deal at the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_div_1/3688565.stm|title=Brechin re-sign duo|date=2004-05-05|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=2008-09-12}}</ref> In the first half of 2005, Forfar rejected approaches from [[Stranraer F.C.|Stranraer]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_div_1/4190133.stm|title=Stranraer lose out on Shields bid |date=2005-01-20|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=2008-09-12}}</ref> and [[Grimsby Town F.C.|Grimsby Town]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/f/forfar_athletic/4078120.stm|title=Forfar dismiss offer for Shields|date=2005-06-09|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=2008-09-12}}</ref> although [[Gillingham F.C.|Gillingham]] secured his signature in a <U+00A3>25,000 deal.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/g/gillingham/4743461.stm|title=Gillingham sign Forfar's Shields|date=2005-08-03|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=2008-09-12}}</ref> Shields made just six league starts for ''The Gills'' before being released in May 2006, and he quickly joined [[Livingston F.C.|Livingston]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/l/livingston/5019452.stm|title=Livi snap up Gillingham's Shields|date=2006-05-26|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=2008-09-12}}</ref>

In August 2007, Shields was released from ''Livi'' on his 26th birthday, allowing him to move with fellow player [[Daryl Smylie]] to [[Sweden|Swedish]] side [[<U+00D6>stersunds FK]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/l/livingston/6948794.stm|title=Striker Matthews wins Livi deal |date=2007-08-15|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=2008-09-12}}</ref>

